# CoDevx Project Rules

## What this repo is

CoDevx is an autonomous AI software development team running as a FastAPI backend (`agent_mesh.py`). It orchestrates 8 specialized agents through a full SDLC pipeline. The Cursor AI assistant should understand this architecture and help you interact with it.

## MCP Server (use this to control the pipeline from Cursor)

CoDevx exposes an MCP server at **`http://localhost:8000/mcp`** when the backend is running.

Available tools:
| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `codevx_submit_order` | Submit a task — triggers the full 8-agent pipeline |
| `codevx_get_state` | Current agent statuses + active task |
| `codevx_get_history` | Completed tasks with files, branch, PR |
| `codevx_get_logs` | Recent activity logs |
| `codevx_get_agent` | Status of a specific named agent |

**Example:** To trigger the pipeline, ask Cursor: _"Use the CoDevx MCP tool to submit an order: build a Stripe billing integration"_

## Architecture (read before editing)

```
agent_mesh.py       ← entire backend, ~1770 lines, intentionally single-file
zeroclaw_squad.yaml ← team config, pipeline settings, storage
command-center/     ← React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind dashboard
docs/               ← architecture docs, ZeroClaw examples
```

## Coding standards to enforce

### Python (`agent_mesh.py`)
- Full PEP 695 type hints everywhere — no untyped functions
- `structlog` for all logging — no `print()` or `logging.info()`
- Async/await throughout — no blocking I/O in async context
- Parameterized SQL only — `db.execute("SELECT ... WHERE id = ?", (id,))`
- HTTPException with sanitized messages — never expose stack traces
- `asyncio.create_subprocess_exec()` for subprocesses — never `shell=True`

### Frontend (`command-center/`)
- Named exports only — no `export default`
- Strict TypeScript — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- React Query (TanStack v5) for server state
- Zod + React Hook Form for all forms
- WCAG 2.1 AA — aria-labels on all interactive elements

### Tests
- ≥85% branch coverage on all new code
- Mock ALL external I/O (`respx` for httpx, `moto` for S3, etc.)
- `httpx.AsyncClient(app=app, base_url="http://test")` for FastAPI integration tests
- At least 1 `hypothesis` property-based test for any data-processing logic

### Security
- Never hardcode secrets — env vars only
- Rate-limit all auth endpoints (login / register / password-reset)
- CORS: never `allow_origins=["*"]` in production
- All file paths must be validated before use (no path traversal)

## Section structure in agent_mesh.py (do not break this)

```
# 1. CONFIGURATION
# 2. DATABASE (SQLite via aiosqlite)
# 3. SHARED STATE
# 4. HELPERS
# 5. LLM ENGINE + AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPTS + AGENT_TEMPERATURES
#    5.5 AGENT MEMORY
#    5.6 REAL TOOL EXECUTION
#    5.7 TASK DECOMPOSITION
# 6. GIT ENGINE
# 7. WHATSAPP
# 7.5 ZEROCLAW GATEWAY
# 8. DISCORD BOT
# 9. EXECUTION PIPELINE (execute_pipeline)
# 10. MCP SERVER (IDE integration: VS Code, Cursor, Antigravity)
# 11. FASTAPI APP + ROUTES
# 12. ENTRY POINT
```

